article.description: Kalen Johnson passed for four touchdowns and ran for another, both career highs, and Howard beat Savannah State 55-9 Saturday to snap a seven-game losing streak.
article.headline: Howard snaps 7-game skid, beats Savannah State, 55-9
article.linkText: Howard snaps 7-game skid, beats Savannah State, 55-9
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Kalen Johnson passed for four touchdowns and ran for another, both career highs, and Howard beat Savannah State 55-9 Saturday to snap a seven-game losing streak. Johnson completed 14 of 20 passes for 219 yards and added 29 yards rushing. Guy Lemonier's 8-yard touchdown run capped a 12-play, 93-yard drive and gave Howard (1-7, 1-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) a 7-0 lead midway through the first quarter. Johnson hit Myles Williams for a 47-yard score and Ricquaz Brannon for a 21-yard touchdown to extend the Bison's lead to 20-0 going into the second quarter. Savannah State (1-6, 1-4) committed four turnovers, two of which were returned for scores. Travon Hunt had a 31-yard fumble return for a touchdown that gave Howard a 41-9 lead late in the third and Kenneth Russ had an 11-yard pick-6 -- just 13 seconds after Johnson's 1-yard scoring run -- to cap the scoring with 9:31 to play.
